'''Jean-Claude Logé''' (born  30 March 1941) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman. He obtained a master's degree in [[business science]] and [[finance]] at the [[Louvain School of Management]] ([[Catholic University of Leuven (1834–1968)|University of Louvain]]) in 1963. In December 1984 Jean-Claude Logé, together with Bernard Lescot and Pierre Herpain, created the [[Information and Communications Technology|ICT]] company [[Systemat]]. In 1996, the readers of the Belgian weekly business magazine ''Trends Tendances'' elected him Manager of the Year.

